Model (FIXED throughout): Germany_Esperstedt_CordedWare <- Russia_Samara_EBA_Yamnaya + Czechia_N_GlobularAmphora 
Right (FIXED throughout): six canonical + Kotias
The ONLY thing that changes is which populations are in the EXTRACT.

PRE-REGISTERED:
  P1. Each thin population collapses the SNP basis by >10%.        [~85%]
  P2. chi^2 FALLS when a thin population enters the extract, while
      random loss of the same magnitude makes it RISE.             [~70%]
  P3. The observed chi^2 lies BELOW the entire random-loss null at
      matched N -- i.e. outside 20/20 replicates.                  [~60%]
  P4. At least one thin population flips the model from REJECTED to
      NOT REJECTED -- a conclusion reversed by a population the model
      never uses.                                                  [~70%]
  FAILURE MODE: if chi^2 rises (as under random loss), the exhibit is
      just power loss and §3 must be retracted.

